---
description: Summarise the findings under a directory using an extension tool
mode: subagent
tools:
  - read
  - finding_store
params:
  findings_dir: string
---
// `tools:` mixes a built-in (`read`) with an extension-registered Pi tool
// (`finding_store`, contributed by an installed Pi extension). This theta is
// `mode: subagent`, so the invocation runs the WHOLE callee in a spawned child
// `pi` process that loads the same extensions — which is why the MODEL can call
// `finding_store` during the query's tool loop below.
//
// Theta CODE cannot call `finding_store` directly in this release: a code-side
// `finding_store(...)` call would refuse to load, fail-closed, with
// `theta/load/extension-tool-unreachable` (the code-side dispatch rung is
// unwired in 0.9.0). Only `read` and `.theta` callables are code-callable here.
// Listing an extension tool whose extension is not installed is a different
// load-time error (`theta/load/unknown-tool`), not a silent no-op.
@`Use finding_store to list the findings under ${findings_dir}, read any file it
references, and report how many findings are still open in one sentence.`
